add new event callback `on_finished``on_finished` callbackn--------------------nYou can override `on_finished` method in the project, the method wouldnbe triggered when the task_queue goes to 0.nnExample 1: when you starts a project to crawl a website with 100 pages,nthe `on_finished` callback will be fired when 100 pages successncrawled or failed after retries.nExample 2: A project with `auto_recrawl` tasks will **NEVER**ntrigger the `on_finished` callback, because time queue willnnever become 0 when auto_recrawl tasks in it.nExample 3: A project with `@every` decorated method will triggernthe `on_finished` callback every time when the new submittedntasks finished.nnclose #403n

use smaller connect_timeoutWhen having temporary network interruption, requests will hang atnconnecting state, at same time, scheduler will continue dispatching newntasks. After network recover, all request sent out in bulk, which mayncause IP ban.nA smaller connect_timeout will reduce the maximum number of requests innconnecting state when network interruption happends.nnconnect_timeout can be set via self.crawl, and timeout will no longernaffect connect_timeout.n
